(570, 1, '2015-12-24 16:43:09', '2015-12-24 21:43:09', '[wolf_col_12]\r\n\r\n[shareaholic app="share_buttons" id="17605417"]\r\n<h1>The Company</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ground-breaking arts and entertainment programming in Toronto</li>\r\n	<li>Broadcast live via <a href="http://www.dailymotion.com/YouAndMedia" target="_blank">Dailymotion’s</a> potential Canadian audience of 5 million and its social media reach of 500,000 US/International.</li>\r\n	<li>Terrific collaboration with social innovators from the Centre for Social Innovation</li>\r\n	<li>Toronto’s top comedic, music and alternative talent featured locally, nationally and internationally</li>\r\n	<li>Features interactive participation among live in studio and online audience #LFTAnnex</li>\r\n	<li>Box Office, FOH, set up and strike staff are all volunteers, many of whom are from Annex Improv’s ranks</li>\r\n	<li>Sponsors and partners include Analytical Engine Interactive, Beau''s All Natural Brewery, Dailymotion Canada and CSI Toronto</li>\r\n	<li>Gratis hummus and chips</li>\r\n	<li>The show’s crew is a mix of professional and emerging technicians-- together they create a high-quality HD live-streaming product</li>\r\n	<li>LFTAnnex is live-streamed around the world on <a href="www.Dailymotion.com/YouAndMedia" target="_blank">Dailymotion/YouAndMedia</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nCo-Producers 2015\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Laurie-Murphy-portrait-colour.jpg"><img class="wp-image-521 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Laurie-Murphy-portrait-colour-255x300.jpg" alt="" width="109" height="128" /></a><strong>LAURIE MURPHY </strong>is a producer and an award-winning public relations practitioner specializing in strategic integrated marketing and communications and project management (<a href="http://www.marram.ca">www.marram.ca</a>). She works in Toronto with artists, cultural organizations and entrepreneurs, such as One Night Only: The Greatest Musical Never Written, Junes Company, The Eros Group, and in Charlottetown, The Community Foundation of PEI. While at Factory, her work was recognized with a Best PR Award for Small Theatre Company in Canada. In Ottawa, Murphy was the Great Canadian Theatre Company’s Director of Marketing &amp; Communications. She also provided administration/research support at the Inuit Art Foundation (Ottawa), and writing and PR support to The Rooms Art Gallery (St. John’s). She has served as an executive board member on provincial and national boards as an artist and public relations practitioner, such as the Canadian Public Relations Society (President Elect, Ottawa/Gatineau and Past President, Prince Edward Island CPRS Chapters), PEI Council of the Arts, TheatrePEI, and PEI Writers’ Guild. A performer, Laurie is a member of SOCAN, the Society of Composers, Songwriters and Music Publishers of Canada, and is a founding member of "Brunswick Stew” improv. Her work in the training, performance and production of improv garnered Murphy three PEI Theatre Festival Awards (best direction, ensemble and musical inventiveness).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Sasha-Wentges-Colour-Photo.jpg"><img class="wp-image-520 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Sasha-Wentges-Colour-Photo-225x300.jpg" alt="" width="110" height="147" /></a>SASHA WENTGES</strong> is a producer, director and award-winning actress. With mea culpa, she has co-produced/facilitated over a decade of lively cabarets in the Montreal scene. She has also directed/produced many theatrical creations, including <em>The Factory Project </em>with Studio 303 and OUT productions in Montreal as well as <em>Collected Stories </em>at the Tarragon Theatre, in Toronto. She is the co-owner of www.createdaily.ca which facilitates expressive arts workshops in the community at large and posts creative weekly challenges on-line. Currently she is completing her graduate school program at the European Graduate School in Saas-Fee, Switzerland, utilizing the expressive arts in peace building and conflict transformation fields. In the world of comedy, she has directed Sheldon Inkol''s run-away hit: <em>Uninvited</em>, which showcased at the New Ideas Festival and the Summerworks Festival. She also had a stint directing the sketch comedy troupe: <em>Boiled Wieners, </em>in <em>Yellow Robot and the Table of Terror at the Poor Alex. </em>She is thrilled to be part of this ensemble as well as co-producing the monthly live streaming events at CSI.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/brian-g-smith.jpg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-201 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/brian-g-smith-150x150.jpg" alt="brian g smith" width="150" height="150" /></a>BRIAN G. SMITH</strong> is a comedy producer, teacher and director. An award-winning alumnus of The Second City, Brian has produced media for television, print, &amp; the interwebs in Canada and the Caribbean. He is owner/director of ''You and Media'', a creative production company in Toronto, and Artistic Director of Annex Improv, Canada''s only Improv School that includes live broadcast performances as part of the curriculum. Brian is also one of Canada''s most well known LiveStreamers for the arts communities. Live, internet broadcasts that he has produced, including “Streamfest” and “Pat''s 24 HRS for The Stephen Lewis Foundation,” have garnered 10s of thousands of live, unique views and raised over $30,000 for charity. (<a href="http://www.anneximprov.com">www.anneximprov.com</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.youandmedia.com">www.youandmedia.com</a>)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1>It Takes A Village...</h1>\r\nThe co-producers, Laurie Murphy (MARRAM Mktg &amp; PR), Sasha Wentges (Mea Culpa Productions) and Brian G. Smith (Annex Improv &amp; You And Media) want to thank our business partners and supporters. “Live from the Annex” recommends them, highly.\r\n\r\nAmsterdam Brewery (July - September)<a href="http://www.beaus.com">\r\nAnalytical Engine Interactive\r\n</a>Beau''s Beer (July - September & December)\r\n<a href="http://socialinnovation.ca/" target="_blank">CSI Annex\r\n</a><a href="http://www.dailymotion.com/ca-en" target="_blank">DailyMotion Canada</a>\r\n\r\nPhotography – Robert Trick Photography\r\nPromotional Video Editing - Paul Wensley\r\nGraphic Design &amp; Logo – Darryl Gold\r\nTech &amp; Floor Crew members have included the following specialists: Peter Ivaskiv, Hassan Khan, Marcella Tomas, Andis Raibacis, Geoff Doner, Brittney Drysdale, Darryl Gold, Lindsay McDonald, Andrew Kines, Dexter Benson-Barnett and Christine McGlade.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<b>Brunswick Stew 2015</b>\r\n\r\nThis troupe if made up of Annex Improv Performance Ensemble members. They comprise the Improv troupe performing in the Live from the Annex monthly shows at CSI Annex.\r\n\r\nJoe Amero\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Joe-Amero-Lumberjack.jpg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-392 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Joe-Amero-Lumberjack-150x150.jpg" alt="Joe Amero Lumberjack" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n<b></b>\r\n\r\n<b>Joe Amero</b> is a proud graduate of the Comedy Writing Program at the Second City Training Centre where he is currently studying improv. Joe is excited to be furthering his studies at Annex Improv and stoked to play with Brunswick Stew. <a href="http://www.joeamero.com/">www.joeamero.com</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNoah Goldstein\r\n\r\n<strong><strong><a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Annex-May-5th-6515.jpg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-406 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Annex-May-5th-6515-150x150.jpg" alt="Annex May 5th-6515" width="150" height="150" /></a></strong></strong><b></b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Noah Goldstein</b> likes playing stuff. He has taken improv classes at Bad Dog and now at Annex Improv and enjoys making up numbers and shapes in his finance role at work.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKate Hodgson\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Kate-Hodgson-photo.jpg"><img class="wp-image-427 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Kate-Hodgson-photo.jpg" alt="Kate Hodgson photo" width="149" height="149" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAn alumni of the Second City improv and longform program, <strong>Kate Hodgson</strong> has been a student and perform improv for the last three years. Performing as part of a troupe and duo, she has joined the Brewsters to expand her skills and continue her study of improv.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nVictoria Kucher\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Victoria-Kucher.jpeg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-391 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Victoria-Kucher-150x150.jpeg" alt="Victoria Kucher" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n\r\n<b>Victoria Kucher</b> is relatively new to Improv but not to performing. She has been acting in and around Toronto for the last 10 years in Theatre, Film and Television. Recently she has been seen on "Schitt''s Creek", "Isaiah''s Birthday" and the comedic short "Double Date".\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTony Lee\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/RT8_5391.jpg"><img class="wp-image-429 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/RT8_5391-300x200.jpg" alt="RT8_5391" width="173" height="115" /></a>\r\n\r\n<b>Tony Lee</b> was born and raised by Annex Improv. He has appeared on stage at Live from the Annex and Comedy Bar in Toronto. To pay for his continuing improv education, Tony works as an advertising writer and creative director.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSteve Lyon\r\n\r\n<img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-403 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Annex-May-5th-6451-1-150x150.jpg" alt="Annex May 5th-6451-1" width="150" height="150" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Steve Lyon</b> is a student of Second City and Annex Improv. He’s appeared onstage at the Comedy Bar and Live from the Annex.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLaurie Murphy\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Annex-May-5th-6615.jpg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-407 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Annex-May-5th-6615-150x150.jpg" alt="Annex May 5th-6615" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n\r\nTrained via the Theatresports League (Halifax) Theatre PEI (Charlottetown) and iO (Chicago and Charlottetown), <b>Laurie Murphy</b> is happy to be back pursuing her artistic passion for long-form improv, studying at Annex Improv and performing as a member of the school’s Brunswick Stew.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPaul Wensley\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/RT8_5372.jpg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-410 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/RT8_5372-150x150.jpg" alt="RT8_5372" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn addition to Brunswick Stew, <b>Paul Wensley</b> has performed in numerous troupes in Canada and the US. His background includes extensive training at Second City Toronto and The Groundlings Los Angeles. As a voice actor, Paul can be heard in numerous cartoon series.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSasha Wentges\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Annex-May-5th-6255.jpg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-396 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Annex-May-5th-6255-150x150.jpg" alt="Annex May 5th-6255" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n\r\n<b>Sasha Wentges </b>is a producer, director and award-winning actress. Currently she is completing her graduate school program at the European Graduate School in Saas-Fee, Switzerland, utilizing the expressive arts in peace building and conflict transformation fields. She is thrilled to be part of Brunswick Stew ensemble.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMatt Corluka\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Matt-Crane-FB-photo.jpg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-443 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Matt-Crane-FB-photo-150x150.jpg" alt="Matt Crane FB photo" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Matt Corluka</strong>’s a comedy performer/writer who’ yelled “Are you not entertained?!” in the Coliseum, once had an asthma attack trying to impress models with his running, and needs to borrow just, like, three or four hundred dollars. 2 of those things are real.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div></blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTom King\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Tom-King.jpg"><img class="wp-image-537 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Tom-King-300x284.jpg" alt="Tom King" width="148" height="140" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Tom King</strong> began his improv training at the Second City and hasn''t been able to kick the habit since. He is also a professional classical/jazz pianist, composer and music director apprentice at the Second City.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDensie Pinto\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-474 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/DenisePinto-150x150.jpg" alt="Photo Denise Pinto" width="150" height="150" /></span></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1"><strong>Denise Pinto</strong> probably won''t get your references to early 80s rock bands but she''ll sing you a song anyway. Moonlighting as a person who makes stuff up on stage, she runs a non-profit during the day and finds she makes stuff up there too. One time she did an Indian accent and now they won''t stop talking about it. </span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTimna Ben-Ari\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/LFTA-Oct-6-2015-RT8_2581.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-547" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/LFTA-Oct-6-2015-RT8_2581-200x300.jpg" alt="LFTA Oct 6 2015 RT8_2581" width="132" height="198" /></a>\r\n\r\nKelli Thompson\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Annex-May-5th-6436.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-401" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Annex-May-5th-6436-300x200.jpg" alt="Annex May 5th-6436" width="192" height="128" /></a>\r\n\r\nBrittney Drysdale\r\n\r\n<strong><strong><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-393 alignnone" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Annex-May-5th-6475-150x150.jpg" alt="Annex May 5th-6475" width="150" height="150" /> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nErin Kang\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/RT8_5352.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-428" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/RT8_5352-300x200.jpg" alt="RT8_5352" width="198" height="132" /></a>\r\n\r\nMo Loufty\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> <a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Annex-May-5th-6377.jpg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-394 alignnone" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Annex-May-5th-6377-150x150.jpg" alt="Annex May 5th-6377" width="150" height="150" /></a></strong></strong>\r\n\r\nDavid Perlman\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Annex-May-5th-6259.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-424" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Annex-May-5th-6259-300x200.jpg" alt="Annex May 5th-6259" width="195" height="130" /></a>\r\n\r\nRicky Singh\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Annex-May-5th-6317.jpg"><img class=" size-thumbnail wp-image-395 alignnone" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Annex-May-5th-6317-150x150.jpg" alt="Annex May 5th-6317" width="150" height="150" /></a>\r\n\r\nKyle Stevenson\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> <a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/RT8_5913.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-434 " src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/RT8_5913-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="210" height="140" /></a></strong></strong>\r\n\r\nWinter Tekenos-Levy\r\n<p class="p1"><a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/BGS-RT8_5917.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-426" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/BGS-RT8_5917-300x200.jpg" alt="BGS RT8_5917" width="216" height="144" /></a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Teachers:</b>\r\n\r\nLisa Merchant\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/66-Live-from-the-Annex-Apr-7-2015-pilot-.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-423" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/66-Live-from-the-Annex-Apr-7-2015-pilot--300x200.jpg" alt="66 Live from the Annex Apr 7 2015 pilot" width="188" height="125" /></a>\r\n\r\nAnnex Improv Performance Ensemble Teacher <b>Lisa Merchant </b>is an actor, improviser, instructor, corporate facilitator, and has been improvising/acting for 28 years. She is a multiple nominee and winner of numerous Canadian Comedy Awards. Lisa was one of the cast of the Gemini-nominated Joe Blow Show. She created and produced Toronto’s longest running comedy festival, March of Dames.  Some television credits include Murdoch Mysteries, Train 48, Listen Missy, Go Girl!, to name a few. She performs monthly in Monkey Toast, the live improvised talk show, now in its 10th year, and in Mixed Company. Lisa is an understudy for the highly-acclaimed Women Fully Clothed. She is a Senior Faculty member at The Second City Training Centre and corporate facilitator with The Second City Works, Bad Dog Theatre and privately.  Additionally, she is extremely proud to have delivered improvisation workshops to Canada’s Olympic Team hopefuls for the London 2012 Summer Games as well as the Sochi 2014 Winter Games. <a href="http://www.lisamerchant.com">www.lisamerchant.com</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBrian G. Smith\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/1399466_10153357840291718_7671296496011277660_o_resize.jpeg"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-390 alignleft" src="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/1399466_10153357840291718_7671296496011277660_o_resize-150x150.jpeg" alt="1399466_10153357840291718_7671296496011277660_o_resize" width="150" height="150" /></a>Annex Improv Director/Founder <strong>Brian G. Smith</strong> is a comedy producer, teacher and director. An award-winning alumnus of The Second City, Brian has produced media for television, print, &amp; the interwebs in Canada and the Caribbean. He is owner/director of ‘You and Media’, a creative production company in Toronto, and Artistic Director of Annex Improv, Canada’s only Improv School that includes live broadcast performances as part of the curriculum. Brian is also one of Canada’s most well known LiveStreamers for the arts communities. Live, internet broadcasts that he has produced, including “Streamfest” and “Pat’s 24 HRS for The Stephen Lewis Foundation,” have garnered 10s of thousands of live, unique views and raised over $30,000 for charity. (<a href="http://www.anneximprov.com">www.anneximprov.com</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.youandmedia.com">www.youandmedia.com</a>)', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-24 16:43:09', '2015-12-24 21:43:09', '', 20, 'http://www.livefromtheannex.com/?p=570', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
