(342, 1, '2016-03-28 00:13:35', '2016-03-28 04:13:35', '[wolf_col_12]\n\n[shareaholic app="share_buttons" id="17605417"]\n<h1>Box office</h1>\nTickets are on a first-come, first-serve basis for the intimate cabaret performance space at the CSI Annex, <em>The Garage</em>, 720 Bathurst Street, Toronto. There are no ticket refunds. To leave a voicemail with any concerns or questions, call 647 883 8460 or send an email to <a href="mailto:livefromtheannex@gmail.com">livefromtheannex@gmail.com</a> and we will strive to reply within 24 hours. Shows are all ages; alcohol is offered for sale by The CSI Cafe to those 19+. The CSI Annex venue is currently not wheelchair accessible. No smoking is permitted. To reach the venue via TTC, take the Bathurst St. streetcar south at Bloor to 720 Bathurst Street. Free hummus and chips are provided to the audience. Shows are live with an approximate running time of two hours, including a 15-20 minute intermission. Shows are photographed, and recorded for live broadcast, and may include audience members within the three-camera shots.\n<div style="width: 100%; text-align: left;">\n\n<div style="width:100%; text-align:left;" ><iframe  src="//eventbrite.ca/tickets-external?eid=18486127505&ref=etckt" frameborder="0" height="214" width="100%" vspace="0" hspace="0" marginheight="5" marginwidth="5" scrolling="auto" allowtransparency="true"></iframe><div style="font-family:Helvetica, Arial; font-size:10px; padding:5px 0 5px; margin:2px; width:100%; text-align:left;" ><a class="powered-by-eb" style="color: #dddddd; text-decoration: none;" target="_blank" href="http://www.eventbrite.ca/r/etckt">Powered by Eventbrite</a></div></div>\n[/wolf_col_12]', 'Tickets', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-03-28 00:13:35', '2016-03-28 04:13:35', '', 22, 'http://www.livefromtheannex.com/?p=342', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(344, 1, '2015-06-13 21:36:23', '2015-06-14 01:36:23', '[wolf_col_12]\r\n\r\n[shareaholic app="share_buttons" id="17605417"]\r\n<h1>Box office</h1>\r\nTickets are on a first-come, first-serve basis for the 75-seat cabaret performance space at the CSI Annex, <em>The Garage</em>, 720 Bathurst Street, Toronto.\r\n\r\nThere are no ticket refunds. To leave a voicemail with any concerns or questions, call 416 619 4621 or send an email to <a href="mailto:livefromtheannex@gmail.com">livefromtheannex@gmail.com</a> and we will strive to reply within 24 hours.\r\n\r\nShows are all ages; alcohol is offered to those 19+ at great prices; the CSI Annex venue is wheelchair accessible; no smoking is permitted; via TTC, south of Bathurst and Bloor.\r\n\r\nFree hummus and chips are provided to the audience. Other food and snacks are also on sale at the venue.\r\n\r\nShows are live with an approximate running time of two hours, including a 15-20 minute intermission. Shows are broadcast live, and may include audience members within the three-camera shots.\r\n\r\n<div style="width:100%; text-align:left;" ><iframe  src="//eventbrite.ca/tickets-external?eid=17333349515&ref=etckt" frameborder="0" height="214" width="100%" vspace="0" hspace="0" marginheight="5" marginwidth="5" scrolling="auto" allowtransparency="true"></iframe><div style="font-family:Helvetica, Arial; font-size:10px; padding:5px 0 5px; margin:2px; width:100%; text-align:left;" ><a class="powered-by-eb" style="color: #dddddd; text-decoration: none;" target="_blank" href="http://www.eventbrite.ca/r/etckt">Powered by Eventbrite</a></div>\r\n\r\n[/wolf_col_12]', 'Tickets', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-13 21:36:23', '2015-06-14 01:36:23', '', 22, 'http://www.livefromtheannex.com/?p=344', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(576, 1, '2016-03-28 00:18:00', '2016-03-28 04:18:00', 'Shows resume in the Fall 2016. Come on back for info this summer! Or send an email to livefromtheannex@gmail.com to chat. \r\n\r\n[wolf_col_12]\r\n[shareaholic app="share_buttons" id="17605417"]\r\n<h1>Buzz and Media Coverage</h1>\r\n<a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Live-from-the-Annexs-Dec-1-line-up-its-final-in-2015-cabaret-series-News-Released-Nov-19-2015.pdf">Live from the Annex''s Dec 1 line up, its final in 2015 cabaret series - News (Released Nov 19, 2015)</a> DECEMBER LI|NE UP! Live from the Annex’s final show in its 2015 series is on December 1<sup>st</sup>. The holiday party show line up includes <strong>Elvira Kurt </strong>(Comic), <strong>David Jones</strong> (Music - Piano), <strong>Karim </strong><strong>Rizkallah </strong>(Music – Halo Drum),<strong> Baker</strong> <strong>&amp; Cawley </strong>(Improv/Sketch), <strong>Sasha Wentges</strong>, <strong>Laurie Murphy</strong> and <strong>Brian G. Smith</strong> (Co-MCs &amp; LFTAnnex Co-Producers) and <strong>‘CSI Annex Pop-Up Market’ </strong>(CSI Profile). In addition, the show features <strong>Brunswick Stew</strong> (<strong>Annex Improv</strong>) with guest improviser <strong>Naomi Snieckus</strong>. ''Live from the Annex'' monthly cabaret features Toronto''s best comedy, music and social innovators. A show blending arts, community and technology with <strong>live streaming</strong> via a video portal, LFTAnnex gives local talent the rare opportunity to shine locally and internationally. (<a href="http://www.dailymotion.com/youandmedia">http://www.dailymotion.com/youandmedia</a>).\r\n\r\n[wolf_last_posts count="10" category="Media"]\r\n\r\n[/wolf_col_12]\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Media', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '26-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-28 00:18:00', '2016-03-28 04:18:00', '', 26, 'http://www.livefromtheannex.com/?p=576', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(499, 3, '2015-10-31 22:37:04', '2015-11-01 02:37:04', '[wolf_col_12]\r\n\r\n[shareaholic app="share_buttons" id="17605417"]\r\n<h1>Box office</h1>\r\nTickets are on a first-come, first-serve basis for the intimate cabaret performance space at the CSI Annex, <em>The Garage</em>, 720 Bathurst Street, Toronto. There are no ticket refunds. To leave a voicemail with any concerns or questions, call 416 619 4621 or send an email to <a href="mailto:livefromtheannex@gmail.com">livefromtheannex@gmail.com</a> and we will strive to reply within 24 hours. Shows are all ages; alcohol is offered for sale by The Coffee Pub to those 19+. The CSI Annex venue is currently not wheelchair accessible. No smoking is permitted. To reach the venue via TTC, take the Bathurst St. streetcar south at Bloor to 720 Bathurst Street. Free hummus and chips are provided to the audience. Shows are live with an approximate running time of two hours, including a 15-20 minute intermission. Shows are photographed, and recorded for live broadcast, and may include audience members within the three-camera shots.\r\n<div style="width: 100%; text-align: left;"><iframe src="//eventbrite.ca/tickets-external?eid=18486129511&amp;ref=etckt" width="100%" height="214" frameborder="0" marginwidth="5" marginheight="5" scrolling="auto"></iframe>\r\n<div style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial; font-size: 10px; padding: 5px 0 5px; margin: 2px; width: 100%; text-align: left;"><a class="powered-by-eb" style="color: #dddddd; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.eventbrite.ca/r/etckt" target="_blank">Powered by Eventbrite</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/wolf_col_12]', 'Tickets', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-10-31 22:37:04', '2015-11-01 02:37:04', '', 22, 'http://www.livefromtheannex.com/?p=499', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(510, 3, '2015-10-31 22:51:10', '2015-11-01 02:51:10', 'I’m always eager to check out any venues that break with the traditional uses of space.My latest experience was this past Tuesday at The Garage, which is located within the Annex’s <a href="http://socialinnovation.ca/">Centre for Social Innovation (CSI)</a>.  Living up to its name, the space, has an open industrial feel, but at the same time a welcoming presence fit for such performances.  The monthly performing arts show, which includes live-streamed comedy and music, made excellent use of this small but intimate space. Also, one can never go wrong with free samples from Beau’s Brewery.  Perhaps most notably, this event also included free hummus; yes, free hummus (Check out the hilarious “<a href="http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x2zoqnv_live-from-the-annex-promo-video_fun">Oh, the hummus” Promo Video</a>). Read more &gt;&gt; <a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Buzz-Mag-Casey-Robertson-Aug-8-2015.pdf">Buzz Mag Casey Robertson Aug 8 2015</a>', 'Buzz Magazine applaudes Cabaret Series in CSI Annex Garage', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '501-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-10-31 22:51:10', '2015-11-01 02:51:10', '', 501, 'http://www.livefromtheannex.com/?p=510', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
