(554, 1, '2015-11-20 09:02:44', '2015-11-20 14:02:44', '[wolf_col_12]\r\n\r\n[shareaholic app="share_buttons" id="17605417"]\r\n<h1>Box office</h1>\r\nTickets are on a first-come, first-serve basis for the intimate cabaret performance space at the CSI Annex, <em>The Garage</em>, 720 Bathurst Street, Toronto. There are no ticket refunds. To leave a voicemail with any concerns or questions, call 416 619 4621 or send an email to <a href="mailto:livefromtheannex@gmail.com">livefromtheannex@gmail.com</a> and we will strive to reply within 24 hours. Shows are all ages; alcohol is offered for sale by The Coffee Pub to those 19+. The CSI Annex venue is currently not wheelchair accessible. No smoking is permitted. To reach the venue via TTC, take the Bathurst St. streetcar south at Bloor to 720 Bathurst Street. Free hummus and chips are provided to the audience. Shows are live with an approximate running time of two hours, including a 15-20 minute intermission. Shows are photographed, and recorded for live broadcast, and may include audience members within the three-camera shots.\r\n<div style="width: 100%; text-align: left;">\r\n\r\n<div style="width:100%; text-align:left;" ><iframe  src="//eventbrite.ca/tickets-external?eid=18486127505&ref=etckt" frameborder="0" height="214" width="100%" vspace="0" hspace="0" marginheight="5" marginwidth="5" scrolling="auto" allowtransparency="true"></iframe><div style="font-family:Helvetica, Arial; font-size:10px; padding:5px 0 5px; margin:2px; width:100%; text-align:left;" ><a class="powered-by-eb" style="color: #dddddd; text-decoration: none;" target="_blank" href="http://www.eventbrite.ca/r/etckt">Powered by Eventbrite</a></div></div>\r\n[/wolf_col_12]', 'Tickets', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-20 09:02:44', '2015-11-20 14:02:44', '', 22, 'http://www.livefromtheannex.com/?p=554', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(561, 3, '2015-11-21 22:27:29', '2015-11-22 03:27:29', 'Live from the Annex’s final show in its 2015 series is on December 1<sup>st</sup>. The holiday party show line up includes <strong>Elvira Kurt </strong>(Comic), <strong>David Jones</strong> (Music - Piano), <strong>Karim </strong><strong>Rizkallah </strong>(Music – Halo Drum),<strong> Baker</strong> <strong>&amp; Cawley </strong>(Improv/Sketch), <strong>Sasha Wentges</strong>, <strong>Laurie Murphy</strong> and <strong>Brian G. Smith</strong> (Co-MCs &amp; LFTAnnex Co-Producers) and <strong>‘CSI Annex Pop-Up Market’ </strong>(CSI Profile). In addition, the show features <strong>Brunswick Stew</strong> (<strong>Annex Improv</strong>) with guest improviser <strong>Naomi Snieckus</strong>. ''Live from the Annex'' monthly cabaret features Toronto''s best comedy, music and social innovators. A show blending arts, community and technology with <strong>live streaming</strong> via a video portal, LFTAnnex gives local talent the rare opportunity to shine locally and internationally. (<a href="http://www.dailymotion.com/youandmedia">http://www.dailymotion.com/youandmedia</a>).  see more&gt;&gt; <a href="http://www.livefromtheannex.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Live-from-the-Annexs-Dec-1-line-up-its-final-in-2015-cabaret-series-News-Released-Nov-19-2015.pdf">Live from the Annex''s Dec 1 line up, its final in 2015 cabaret series - News (Released Nov 19, 2015)</a>', 'Dec 1 Artists Announced: Elvira Kurt, Lisa Merchant, Naomi Snieckus, Baker & Cawley, David Jones & Brunswick Stew', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dec-1-artists-announced-elvira-kurt-lisa-merchant-naomi-snieckus-baker-cawley-david-jones-brunswick-stew', '', '', '2015-11-21 22:27:29', '2015-11-22 03:27:29', '', 0, 'http://www.livefromtheannex.com/?p=561', 0, 'post', '', 0),
