(569, 1, '2015-12-24 16:37:28', '2015-12-24 21:37:28', '[shareaholic app="share_buttons" id="17605417"]\r\n<h2>Live From The Annex</h2>\r\n2015 NOW Magazine Award Nominee for Toronto’s Best Comedy Club\r\n\r\nLive from the Annex 2016 is taking a short holiday from its monthly shows until the spring. Visit again for programming updates! \r\n\r\nLaurie Murphy, Sasha Wentges and Brian G. Smith co-produced ''Live from the Annex'' 2015, a monthly cabaret series featuring Toronto’s top disparate entertainers in comedy, music and alternative entertainment. The series rans the first Tuesday of every month, from 8 – 10 p.m., at CSI Annex, in the Garage, 720 Bathurst Street (just south of Bloor street), Toronto. Artists included an emcee, comic artist(s), sketch comedy troupe, a musical guest, and the series’ resident improv troupe Brunswick Stew. The shows were broadcast live via <a href="http://www.Dailymotion.com/YouAndMedia">www.Dailymotion.com/YouAndMedia.</a>\r\n\r\n<b>Artists:</b>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Music:</strong></em> April 7 Pilot - Erika Werry; May 5 Official Opening - Drew Smith (Dr Ew); June 2 - Mia Sheard, Rick Miller &amp; Steph Baptist with Todd Lumley (Mr. Lonely), Lee Cohen; July 7 - Asher Ettinger, Everyone Loves Marineland; Aug 4 - Deadmouse, The Musical; Sept 1 - Salon Des Refuses; Oct 6 - The Boxcar Boys; Nov 3 - Avro; Dec 1 - David Jones with Karim Rizkallah.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Comic and Sketch Artists</strong></em>: March 25 Dress Rehearsal Isaac Kessler, Rob Trick; April 7 Pilot - MC Ben Beauchemin, Fratwurst; May 5 Official Opening Colin Sharpe, The Templeton Philharmonic, Keystone Theatre; May 5 - 2-Man, No-Show, BOOM''s Rick Miller, Poet Stephaine Baptist; July 7 - MC Ron Pederson, Chris Funk – The Wonderist, Two Juliets, Gavin Crawford<span class="aBn" tabindex="0" data-term="goog_1837732358"><span class="aQJ">; Sept 1 - Stepping in for Tony Ho... The Weaker Vessels, Sarah Hiller, Matt Folliott, Keesha Brownie; Oct 6 - Morro and Jasp, MC Mary Ellen MacLean, Boylesque''s James and the Giant Pasty, Red Herring, A Professional Distraction; Nov 3 - MC Sasha Wentges, IAN THE POET, Silvi Santoso, Plum Thunder </span></span>; Dec 1 - MCs Laurie Murphy, Brian G. Smith & Sasha Wentges, Naomi Smieckus, Rob Baker & Adam Cawley, Elvira Kurt. \r\n\r\n<b>CSI Members &amp; Other Special Guest Profiles: </b>Apr 7 -<b> </b>Reel Canada; May 5 - Action against Hunger; June 2 - The Concerned Kids; July 7 - Jayu; Aug 4 - Our Horizon, SummerWorks; Sept 1 - Canadian Comedy Awards; Oct 6 - Green Majority; Nov 3 - CSI; Dec 1 - Erin Kang/CSI Annex Holiday Pop-Up Holiday Market.\r\n\r\n<b>Crew Members: </b>Marcella Tomas, Lindsey McDonald, Andis Raibacis, Geoff Doner, Brittney Drysdale, Darryl Gold, Andrew Kines, Bryson Winchester, Paul Shoebridge, Christine McGlade, Dexter Benson Barnett, Hassan Khan Zada and more!\r\n\r\n<b>Volunteers, </b>the heart of our organization - we could not do it without you!: Janice Wilson, Jan Keck, Erin Kang, Danielle Benton, Monique Stuive, Chris Warren, Kate Hodgson, Alanna Reba, Linda Palmer Nye, Tom Burns, Cameron McGlade and of course The Stewies!\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h1 style="text-align: left;">Contact Us at <a href="mailto:livefromtheannex@gmail.com" target="_blank">livefromtheannex@gmail.com</a></h1>\r\nIf you would like to be considered as a performer/act in one of our 2016 shows, or if you would like to join our team, as a volunteer or an intern, or are interested in investing in us and our TO arts production, please send us an email at <a href="mailto:livefromtheannex@gmail.com" target="_blank">livefromtheannex@gmail.com.\r\n</a>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">[wolf_button url="mailto:livefromtheannex@gmail.com" color="white" type="flat" size="medium"]Email Now[/wolf_button]</p>', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-24 16:37:28', '2015-12-24 21:37:28', '', 12, 'http://www.livefromtheannex.com/?p=569', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
